HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 405
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Paris Saint-Germain Football Club on winning its
second consecutive UEFA Champions League title
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Paris Saint-Germain Football Club on winning its second consecutive UEFA
3 Champions League title.
4 WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain Football Club lifted the UEFA Champions League
5 Trophy for the second consecutive year after a 4-3 penalty shootout victory over Arsenal in
6 the final of the 2025-2026 Champions League at Puskas Arena in Budapest, Hungary; and
7 WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain Football Club, known by fans as Les Rouge-et-
8 Bleu, were cheered to victory by seventeen thousand fans in attendance at the game in
9 Budapest, and thousands more across France and the rest of the world; and
10 WHEREAS, with the addition of the 2026 UEFA Champions League Trophy, Paris
11 Saint-Germain has fifty-seven domestic and international titles in its trophy cabinet; it also
12 defended its French Ligue 1 title during the 2025-2026 season; and
13 WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain fielded the second-youngest squad during the
14 2025-2026 Champions League; the club relied on its incredible attacking depth and tied its
15 own record of seven players involved in at least five goals throughout the tournament; and
16 WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain Football Club is led by its president, Nasser Al-
17 Khelaïfi, and the men's team is managed by Luis Enrique; the team's goalkeepers are Matvei
18 Safonov, Lucas Chevalier, and Renato Marin; the defenders are Achraf Hakimi, Marquinhos,
19 Lucas Hernandez, Nuno Mendes, Lucas Beraldo, Illia Zabarnyi, and Willian Pacho; the
20 midfielders are Fabián Ruiz, Vitinha, Lee Kang-in, Senny Mayulu, Dro Fernández, Warren
21 Zaïre-Emery, and João Neves; and the forwards are Khvicha Kvaratskhelia, Gonçalo Ramos,
